To learn more and access additional features, download the Amazon Alexa App.
How to use & Precautions to take
Not all devices are supported. Use the trial version to check compatibility.
Try for 7 days free of charge. \n\nPlease follow the \"How to use\" instructions that will be displayed next to make sure that each feature can be detected.
Would you like to continue using your settings from the trial? If not you will begin from the initial setup.

・This feature only supports landscape display mode, please use the device on its side.
・When using this feature, please secure your device with a proper cradle.
・This feature uses your camera and location services settings to operate. Please be careful, as the feature will not work if the settings are turned OFF.
・Depending on the device or the situation, the device can overheat and cause a forced shutdown. In some cases using the air-condition for cool air flow can alleviate this.
・Please close out all other applications if you experience instability, as this feature requires a lot of memory. If this does not correct the issue, please restart the device. 
・Using all the features can significantly use up the battery. We recommend connecting to a charger or conserving battery life by lowering the backlight on your display.
・Do not leave your device in the car in hot temperatures. To prevent any issues, refer to your device's user manual for proper operation.
・Depending on the usage and environment, the device can heat up and automatically close out and stop working.
・We assume no responsibility, if the device stops functioning due to any malfunction or model changes, even after the purchase of this feature.
・We recommend you check to see if your device is supported before purchasing this feature.

[Installation Notes]
・Please be sure to use correct equipment for mounting. 
・Please mount the device securely where it will not obstruct driving. 
・For accurate readings, secure the device both vertically and horizontally. 
・Avoid installing in locations that would interfere with the deployment of the airbag. Interference may prevent the airbag from functioning correctly during a traffic collision. 

[Locations for device installation]
・Position the device as close as possible to the centre of the width of the vehicle.
・Position the device on the dashboard where there are no reflections.
・Position the camera lens so that it points within the area of the wiper.

[Adjusting the camera direction]
Always adjust the camera when attaching the device. 
・Adjust the device straight in the same direction of the vehicle.
・Adjust the device both vertically and horizontally until the OK button is displayed in the centre of the screen. 

[Setting the installation conditions]
・Please set the distance from the camera to the front end of the vehicle. 
・Please set the vehicle width. 
・Please set the height from the ground to the camera. 

[Display of operating status]
Depending on the operating status, an icon is displayed
・Functioning
・Detecting
・Error
※By touching the Error icon, you can check the error messages. 

In case of a warning, a warning dialogue is displayed. 
※The warning dialogue will be displayed only on the screen on which the icon is displayed.

・Please secure the device with a proper cradle.
・Secure the device where it does not obstruct your view when driving.
・For accurate reading secure the device horizontally & vertically.
・Please do not set the device anywhere that would obstruct the airbag safety system. Setting the device where it could interfere with the airbag system may cause it not to deploy or cause injury.
